#Text=Wikimedian activist Adrianne Wadewitz dies
#Text=This article mentions the Wikimedia Foundation , one of its projects , or people related to it .
#Text=Wikinews is a project of the Wikimedia Foundation .
#Text=Thursday , April 10 , 2014
#Text=A video from 2012 where Wadewitz discusses the impact of Wikipedia Image : Vgrigas .
#Text=News broke early this morning on Facebook that Wikipedian Adrianne Wadewitz died while rock climbing recently .
#Text=Wadewitz was well known in the Wikimedia community for her activism drawing attention to the lack of female contributors on Wikipedia .
#Text=She was also very involved in the Wiki Education Foundation , serving as a member of its board of directors .

#Text=Wadewitz was one of the most visible women in the media on the under-representation of women amongst contributors to Wikipedia , talking to media organizations like the BBC , the Huffington Post and non-English publications like Greek-language magazine LIFO .
#Text=Some estimates put female participation rates at around 10 % of contributors and there is a body of academic work talking about systemic bias against topics featuring women on Wikipedia .

#Text=She was involved in organizing several edit-a-thons aimed at encouraging greater female participation and improving content about women , including Wikipedia Takes America : Los Angeles , FemTech Edit-a-thon , Wikipedia Loves Eagle Rock , Wikipedia Loves WeHo , and Feminists Engage Wikipedia .
#Text=Wadewitz 's own work to address systemic bias as an article contributor included improving English Wikipedia articles relating to women , including :
#Text=Adrianne embodied brilliance , determination , and enthusiasm in everything she did — Tribute by a fellow Wikimedian
#Text=Mary Wollstonecraft
#Text=Thoughts on the Education of Daughters
#Text=Mary : A Fiction
#Text=A Vindication of the Rights of Woman
#Text=Maria : or , The Wrongs of Woman
#Text=Timeline of Mary Wollstonecraft
#Text=Fanny Imlay
#Text=Mary Shelley
#Text=Anna Laetitia Barbauld
#Text=Sarah Trimmer
#Text=Mary Martha Sherwood
#Text=The funerary arrangement picture decorating the top of Wadewitz 's Wikipedia talk page .
#Text=Image : Mogens Engelund .
#Text=She started contributing to English Wikipedia in July 2004 .

#Text=She had taught two classes on collaborative work on the project , and was involved with FemTechNet Wikistorming , an academic effort to encourage more women involved in academia to contribute to Wikipedia .

#Text=In the past month , she had written several blog entries on HASTAC , an online collaborative platform dedicated to changing the way people learn , about how to write about academics on Wikipedia .
#Text=Fellow activist Sarah Stierch said in a public post on Facebook , " My heart hurts .
